The info there is not PII, there is no way to identify the person, so the LOPD/GDPR/etc doesn't really apply. No ids, and no links to your profile, email, whatever.
The only exception is if, in "Location" (text field), someone could write something like "_I'm John Doe and my DNI is 123456789A_".

> *Personal data*, also known as *personal information* or *personally identifiable information (PII)* is any information relating to an identifiable person.
> Personal data is defined under the GDPR as "any information which [is] related to an *identified or identifiable* natural person".
> <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Personally_identifiable_information>
